Reasoning: The paper discusses a stylized model of online social networks and investigates the spread of low-quality information. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the impact of information overload and limited attention, which could also place it in the sub-categories of Systems and Control (cs.SY) or Multimedia (cs.MM). The paper also mentions the spread of digital misinformation, which could place it in the sub-categories of Cybersecurity (cs.CY) or Computation and Language (cs.CL). Finally, the paper discusses the relationship between quality and popularity of information, which could place it in the sub-category of Software Engineering (cs.SE).
